# Security-critical rules (current codebase)

## 1) Local API access enforcement

When a Local API call is made on behalf of authenticated user, always pass both:

- `user`
- `overrideAccess: false`

Without `overrideAccess: false`, Payload bypasses collection access controls.

## 2) Hook transaction safety

In hooks, pass `req` to nested `req.payload.*` operations so work remains in same transaction scope.

## 3) Hook loop prevention

If hook writes back to same collection/doc, use context flag guard to prevent recursive loops.

## 4) Gateway auth forwarding

CMS app gateway forwarder (`src/app/api/gateway/[[...route]]/route.ts`) injects `Authorization: JWT ...` from Payload cookie when missing. Preserve this behavior when changing gateway proxying.
